main event: Multiple civilian witnesses reported sighting a bright, egg-shaped object with a rapid fluttering motion near Camden, New Jersey on May 17, 18, 19, and 21, 1964.
interesting points: The object changed colors, starting as bright red, then turning yellow and green.
The object appeared to hover and then move rapidly towards the west.
The sightings lasted for 10-20 minutes each time.
A Navy P2V Neptune aircraft with a searchlight was in the area at the time of the sightings.
The report suggests the object could have been the Echo satellite or the P2V aircraft itself.
witnesses: Multiple civilian witnesses, including a commercial photographer and another unidentified observer
photographs: No photographs were included in the report
